            <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
                <lb n="2"/><persName><name type="gentilicium" key="Petronius">Petronio</name> <name type="cognomen" key="Castor">Castori</name></persName>,
                <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr><hi rend="apex">e</hi><hi rend="apex">q</hi></abbr><ex>uiti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr><hi rend="apex">R</hi></abbr><ex>omano</ex></expan>, qui vixit <expan><abbr>ann</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
                <lb n="4"/><num value="80">LXXX</num>, diebus <num value="30">XXX</num>;
                <lb n="5"/>patri <expan><abbr><hi rend="apex">b</hi></abbr><ex>ene</ex></expan> <expan><abbr><hi rend="apex">m</hi></abbr><ex>erenti</ex></expan> fecit
                <lb n="6"/><persName><name type="gentilicium" key="Valerius"><expan><abbr>Val</abbr><ex>erius</ex></expan></name> <name type="cognomen" key="Anatolius">Anatolius</name></persName>, <expan><abbr>mil</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan>
                <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> <num value="2" type="ordinal">II</num> Herculiae.
            </ab>
            </div>
             <div type="translation">
                 <p>"To the divine shades. Valerius Anatolius, solider of the second legion Herculia, made this for Petronius Castor, Rome eques, his well-deserving father, who lived 80 years, 30 days."</p>
             </div>
            <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>Line 3: abbreviation for "equiti Romano" marked with apices. Line 5: abbreviation for
                    "bene merenti" marked with apices. Line 6: slight reverse indentation at line
                    beginning, but does not appear intentional. </p></div>
            
